SIMPLE: stereomonoscope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stereomonoscope
<hw>Ste`re*o*mon"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stereo-</ets> + <ets>mono-</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An instrument with two lenses, by which an image of a single
picture projected upon a screen of ground glass is made to present an
appearance of relief, and may be viewed by several persons at
once.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stereoplasm</ent>⟦br⟧
